 Much?</b></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1656945244430" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1656945244430"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">How many scoops of protein powder per shake or per day you may use depends on your protein needs and your overall meal plan. We recommend 2 scoops of protein as the maximum amount of supplementation per day. Get the rest of your protein from whole foods.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1671474618569" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1671474618569"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Is One Scoop of Protein Powder Enough?</b></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1656945317455" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1656945317455"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">If your total protein needs are low-to-moderate (110-150 grams per day) and you eat high-protein whole foods in every main meal, one scoop per day may be enough.</p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1677835437708" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liqui